section.section:
Restrictions that may be imposed under paragraph (1)(iii) of this subsection include:
Type of highways where the licensee may drive;
Maximum speed limits under which driving is allowed;
Maximum driving distances; and
Other factors that the Administration determines appropriate.

An individual licensed under this section may apply to eliminate the daylight only restriction if the individual:
Has been licensed under this section for at least 1 year;
During the previous year, has not committed a traffic infraction or been involved in a traffic accident where the licensee was at fault;
Has passed a nighttime vision test prescribed by the Administration; and
Has received a driver's training certificate based on nighttime driving skills, from an entity that the Administration has determined is qualified to evaluate drivers under this section.
